FTIR spectrum was acquired to determine the surface functional groups of the C-dots (Fig. 4
                        ). The peak associated with the stretching vibrations of carbonyl groups (CO) were found at 1738cm−1 and 1635cm−1 
                        [3,22]. The peaks at 1255cm−1, 2925cm−1 and 3410cm−1 were assigned to the stretching vibrations of C–O–C, C–H and O–H groups, respectively [22,24]. Consequently, the C-dots are hydrophilic and stable in aqueous solution due to their functional groups containing oxygen.
